description: This file serves as the entry point for a React application. It imports necessary modules, such as React, ReactDOM, and the main App component, then initializes the React app by rendering <App /> within the DOM element with id 'root'.

methods.name: ReactDOM.createRoot
methods.description: Creates a React root to enable rendering the React component tree into the specified DOM element.

methods.name: root.render
methods.description: Renders the React component tree (here: <React.StrictMode><App /></React.StrictMode>) into the DOM.
